text.section:
In addition to the duties set forth elsewhere in this title, the Board shall:
Maintain a registry of all counselors or therapists currently licensed or certified by the Board and all individuals currently working as trainees in accordance with § 17-406(b) of this title;
Submit an annual report to the Governor and the Secretary;
Adopt a code of ethics that the Board considers to be appropriate and applicable to the counselors or therapists currently certified or licensed by the Board and the individuals currently working as trainees in accordance with § 17-406(b) of this title;
Establish continuing education requirements for the counselors or therapists currently certified or licensed by the Board;
Adopt an official seal; and
Create committees as it deems appropriate to advise the Board on special issues.
